docs.lead_paragraph: You heard it here first. City Room is going to make the call that "Jayden" (spelled that way) will be the most popular name for newborn baby boys in New York City sometime in the next two or three years. (See the chart below for the most popular New York baby names for 2007.)Jayden-with-a-Y is already ranked No. 2 in this chart, after breaking the top 10 for the first time ever last year.
